    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Curry</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Curry asks whether the amount mentioned in his telegram regarding the
                        Mora claim is acceptable. If so, he thinks it important to bring the matter
                        to an immediate close.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
